    {
      "id": "2d19a9b3_b010b6b1",
      "file_path": "ansible/roles/firewall/defaults/main.yml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 3,
      "message": "Default value is just it - a default value. You define it to eliminate the need to apply dirty conditionals like \"{var} is defined\" in tasks. Once var is assigned a default value you can be sure it won't be undefined and won't cause play to crash under certain circumstances.\n\nIf we add firewall-enable.yml then the user which wants it to be played has to override it in his favourite way: cmd line, group_vars, @settings_file. No need to modify defaults!",
